&lt;p&gt;BACK OFFICE OPERATIONS MANAGER&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A CAREER WITH POINT72’S BACK OFFICE OPERATIONS TEAM&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Point72, the Back Office Operations team is responsible for the daily reconciliation of all cash balances in Point72’s accounting system to prime brokers on a T+1 basis. The team is responsible for ensuring that all bookings, trade and non-trade related activities are recorded accurately and appropriately. In addition, this team is responsible for reference data maintenance and management.&lt;br&gt;WHAT YOU’LL DO&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Serve as the founding hire and leader of a newly established reconciliations and operational control function, with full ownership to recruit, develop, and manage a team&lt;br&gt;• Design and implement a scalable operating model to support a global, fast paced investment organization, including coverage, controls, escalation paths, and service-level standards.&lt;br&gt;• Own and oversee daily reconciliations; supervise issue investigation and resolution and ensure timely resolution of breaks.&lt;br&gt;• Establish performance management frameworks, including KPIs, quality metrics, and continuous improvement processes to measure team effectiveness and operational excellence.&lt;br&gt;• Partner closely with Technology to define requirements, design, test, and deploy system enhancements; improve existing workflows; and build new processes to streamline and automate reconciliations.&lt;br&gt;• Work closely with prime brokers, custodians, administrators, and other third parties to timely resolve breaks.&lt;br&gt;• Act as a senior escalation point for complex breaks, working directly with counterparties and internal stakeholders to drive resolution.&lt;br&gt;• Identify, prioritize, and deliver automation and straight through processing initiatives to improve efficiency, scalability, and control.&lt;br&gt;• Build strong partnerships across Trading, Compliance, Stock Loan, Legal, Risk, Financial Reporting, Tax, Regulatory Reporting, and Technology to resolve issues and enhance end to end operational outcomes.&lt;br&gt;• Embed a strong control mindset, ensuring processes meet regulatory, audit, and internal risk management standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;WHAT’S REQUIRED?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Bachelor’s degree in finance, Business, Mathematics, or a related field (preferred)&lt;br&gt;• 15+ years of Operations experience within a hedge fund, asset manager, bank, or fund administrator, including demonstrated leadership and ownership of complex operational functions.&lt;br&gt;• Strong product knowledge across equities, futures, equity swaps, FX, derivatives, and fixed income instruments.&lt;br&gt;• Proven experience building, scaling, and managing teams, including hiring, coaching, and performance management.&lt;br&gt;• Advanced technical aptitude, with the ability to partner effectively with Technology and drive system and process improvements.&lt;br&gt;• Exceptional problem solving, analytical, and critical thinking skills, with the ability to operate with urgency and sound judgment.&lt;br&gt;• Strong time management and prioritization skills in a high volume, deadline driven environment.&lt;br&gt;• Highly detail oriented, proactive, and self directed, with a strong sense of ownership and accountability.&lt;br&gt;• Hands-on leader capable of operating at different organizational levels&lt;br&gt;• Excellent written, verbal, and interpersonal communication skills, with the ability to influence across functions and levels.&lt;br&gt;• Advanced proficiency in Excel and the MS Office Suite.&lt;br&gt;• Commitment to the highest ethical standards&lt;/p&gt;
