&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB TITLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Identity Remediation and Onboarding Lead&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A CAREER WITH POINT72&#39;S TECHNOLOGY TEAM &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Point72 reimagines the future of investing, our Technology team is constantly improving our company’s IT infrastructure, positioning us at the forefront of a rapidly evolving technology landscape. We’re a team of experts experimenting, discovering new ways to harness the power of open-source solutions, and embracing enterprise agile methodology. We encourage professional development to ensure you bring innovative ideas to our products while satisfying your own intellectual curiosity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL DO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead enterprise-wide identity remediation initiatives and manage a team of analysts to eliminate orphaned accounts, stale access, excessive privileges, and unmanaged service accounts, delivering measurable and sustained risk reduction across critical systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with the Head of AIM Governance to translate strategic direction, policy requirements, and risk priorities into scalable remediation and onboarding execution plans.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical oversight and selective hands-on execution across account, entitlement, and privileged access cleanup efforts, ensuring alignment with firm standards and least-privilege principles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive service account security improvements, including remediation of clear-text credentials, credential vaulting and rotation, ownership validation, and enforcement of lifecycle controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee onboarding of applications and privileged accounts into the firm’s Identity Governance &amp;amp; Administration (IGA) and Privileged Access Management (PAM) platforms, establishing standardized onboarding processes and validation frameworks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strengthen group and entitlement governance by simplifying complex access structures and aligning them to standardized access models.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with application, infrastructure, and engineering teams to implement access changes, close control gaps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee operational intake channels and remediation pipelines, ensuring appropriate prioritization, escalation, and stakeholder communication, along with developing repeatable remediation playbooks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and report key remediation metrics, risk reduction outcomes, and maintain audit-ready documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify automation opportunities and leverage AI tools and analytics to scale remediation efforts and improve operational efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT&#39;S REQUIRED&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of experience in IAM, identity operations, information security, or related technology disciplines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience leading identity remediation, hygiene, or access risk reduction programs in a complex enterprise environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience managing global or distributed teams, including performance management and workload prioritization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong working knowledge of SailPoint (or equivalent IGA platform), including application onboarding, entitlement management, and remediation workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with Privileged Access Management (PAM) solutions (e.g., CyberArk or similar), including service account onboarding and credential security practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep understanding of least-privilege principles, service account risk management, and administrative access reduction strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting audits and regulatory reviews, including executive-level reporting and defensible control evidence.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong program management skills with the ability to manage multiple concurrent initiatives and deliver measurable outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication skills with the ability to engage technical teams and senior stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leveraging automation, analytics, or AI tools to improve identity operations efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to the highest ethical standards.&lt;/li&gt;
