&lt;p&gt;A CAREER WITH POINT72’S TECHNOLOGY TEAM&lt;br&gt;As Point72 reimagines the future of investing, our Technology team is constantly evolving our firm’s IT infrastructure and engineering capabilities, positioning us at the forefront of a rapidly evolving technology landscape. We’re a team of experts who experiment and work to discover new ways to harness open-source solutions, modern cloud architectures, and sophisticated Artificial Intelligence (AI) solutions, while embracing enterprise agile methodologies. Our commitment to building and innovating in the AI space provides the framework intended to drive smarter decision making and enhance how we build and operate our platforms and applications.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;As a member of Point72’s Technology team, we encourage and support your professional development from day one—helping you advance your technical skills, contribute innovative ideas, and satisfy your own intellectual curiosity—all while delivering real business impact for our multi-billion-dollar global business.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;WHAT YOU’LL DO&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Design, develop, and maintain high-quality iOS applications using Swift, React Native, and modern frameworks (SwiftUI, UIKit).&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Translate product requirements, wireframes, and user flows into polished, responsive iOS features.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Collaborate with UX, product, backend, and release teams to deliver seamless end-to-end solutions.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Optimize applications for performance, accessibility, scalability, and cross-device compatibility.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Ensure code quality through testing, code reviews, troubleshooting, and adherence to engineering best practices.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Improve application architecture, contribute to shared component libraries, and evolve design systems.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Identify, mitigate, and resolve risks related to application and infrastructure changes.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Lead R&amp;amp;D, proofs of concept, and evaluations of new platforms, tools, frameworks, and techniques aligned with business goals.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Coordinate regular and emergency releases while monitoring progress across all project stages.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Maintain compliance with firm-wide software development processes and produce clear technical documentation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;WHAT’S REQUIRED&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;6+ years of engineering experience in the mobile app development business and environment with a passion for building mission-critical, elegantly engineered, and scalable code.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Excellent technical knowledge in Swift, SwiftUI, React Native, and UIKit.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Self-motivated and dedicated attitude with the ability to take ownership of the tasks assigned and deliver them within a reasonable time.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Professional, precise communication skills.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Ability to create self-contained, reusable, and testable modules and components.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Practice clean coding practices (SOLID, continuous refactoring, testing) with experience writing extensive unit tests using automated TDD tasks.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Comfort operating in a fast-paced, agile environment.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Fluency with Git source code management.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Creating configuration, build, and test scripts for Continuous Integration environments.&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Commitment to the highest ethical standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;WE TAKE CARE OF OUR PEOPLE&lt;br&gt;We invest in our people, their careers, their health, and their well-being. When you work here, we provide:&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Fully-paid health care benefits&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Generous parental and family leave policies&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Volunteer opportunities&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Support for employee-led affinity groups representing women, people of color and the LGBT+ community&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Mental and physical wellness programs&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Tuition assistance&lt;br&gt;• &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;A 401(k) savings program with an employer match and more&lt;/p&gt;
