&lt;p&gt;A Career with Point72&#39;s Technology Team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Point72 reimagines the future of investing, our Technology team is constantly evolving our firm’s IT infrastructure and engineering capabilities, positioning us at the forefront of a rapidly evolving technology landscape. We’re a team of experts who experiment and work to discover new ways to harness open-source solutions, modern cloud architectures, and sophisticated Artificial Intelligence (AI) solutions, while embracing enterprise agile methodologies. Our commitment to building and innovating in the AI space provides the framework intended to drive smarter decision making and enhance how we build and operate our platforms and applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a member of Point72’s Technology team, we encourage and support your professional development from day one—helping you advance your technical skills, contribute innovative ideas, and satisfy your own intellectual curiosity—all while delivering real business impact for our multi-billion-dollar global business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL DO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and lead the global real-time communications strategy and roadmap to support the firm’s trading, research, and collaboration needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and scale enterprise-grade trader voice and trading-floor communications platforms that deliver low-latency, high-availability, and measurable business impact&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, recruit, and mentor a large, cross-functional team of engineers, operators, and product managers to deliver continuous improvement and operational excellence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and execute end-to-end migrations to cloud telephony and contact center platforms, including planning, cutover, and post-deployment optimization&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with trading desks, business leaders, and security teams to translate business requirements into resilient, auditable communications services and service-level agreements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage relationships with major vendors and service providers, negotiating contracts and driving vendor accountability for delivery and support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive operational readiness through incident response, capacity planning, monitoring, change control, and fault-tolerant architecture for real-time voice and collaboration services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee architecture, security, and compliance for all real-time communications components, ensuring integration with enterprise networking and identity systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Set performance metrics, manage budgets, and deliver measurable improvements in availability, latency, and user experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT&#39;S REQUIRED&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree&amp;nbsp;in computer science, engineering, telecommunications, or a related field, or equivalent technical experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of hands-on experience&amp;nbsp;in enterprise telephony, real-time communications, or voice technology roles, including&amp;nbsp;designing and deploying cloud telephony at enterprise scale&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience leading large, cross-functional technical teams&amp;nbsp;responsible for both operations and engineering&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct experience with trader voice systems&amp;nbsp;and trading-floor communications operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience implementing and operating telephony and collaboration platforms, including BT, Cisco, Cloud9, Unigy, Zoom, and enterprise contact center solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven experience managing carrier and vendor relationships, circuit lifecycles, and delivering&amp;nbsp;large-scale voice projects with measurable outcomes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong technical expertise in voice networking, including SIP and related protocols, session border controllers, and&amp;nbsp;voice quality management for real-time services&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong program management, stakeholder engagement, and written and verbal communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Based in New York or Stamford, Connecticut, with availability for after-hours support and major deployments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to the highest ethical standards&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WE TAKE CARE OF OUR PEOPLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We invest in our people, their careers, their health, and their well-being. When you work here, we provide:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fully-paid health care benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous parental and family leave policies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Volunteer opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support for employee-led affinity groups representing women, people of color and the LGBT+ community&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mental and physical wellness programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tuition assistance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A 401(k) savings program with an employer match and more&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT POINT72&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Point72 is a leading global alternative investment firm led by Steven A. Cohen. Building on more than 30 years of investing experience, Point72 seeks to deliver superior returns for its investors through fundamental and systematic investing strategies across asset classes and geographies. We aim to attract and retain the industry&#39;s brightest talent by cultivating an investor-led culture and committing to our people&#39;s long-term growth. For more information, visit https://point72.com/.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The annual base salary range for this role is $250,000-$300,000 (USD) , which does not include discretionary bonus compensation or our comprehensive benefits package. Actual compensation offered to the successful candidate may vary from posted hiring range based upon geographic location, work experience, education, and/or skill level, among other things.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ROLE:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Market Data Solutions Specialist will play a critical role in managing and optimizing Point72’s market data ecosystem, serving as the primary bridge between external data providers, internal stakeholders, and technical teams. This individual will ensure that market data feeds, licensing, and policies are aligned with the firm’s trading and investment objectives, while maintaining strict adherence to governance and compliance standards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will combine strong relationship management skills, operational discipline, technical proficiency, and strategic vision to ensure that Point72’s market data environment supports global investment activities effectively and efficiently.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RESPONSIBILITIES:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and Manage External Relationships: Build and maintain strong partnerships with exchanges, vendors, and feed providers; negotiate favorable agreements; and monitor changes in service, policy, and product offerings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enhance Internal Collaboration: Partner closely with Investment Teams, Compliance, Legal, Finance, and Technology to manage day-to-day market data requests, operational processes, and governance adherence. Identify and communicate the impact of exchange and vendor changes on trading workflows, infrastructure, and data strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee Operations &amp;amp; Compliance: Administer market data feed permissions, manage exchange audits, and ensure the firm’s data access and usage is compliant with licensing agreements; monitor and analyze data notifications and policy changes to maintain operational readiness and governance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive Technical Implementation: Collaborate with Technology teams to collaborate testing and integration of real-time data feeds; lead cross-functional projects to improve data infrastructure, efficiency, reliability, and cost-effectiveness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide Strategic Insights &amp;amp; Governance: Monitor industry trends, risks, and opportunities; contribute to the firm’s market data strategy; and ensure compliance with evolving data governance policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;REQUIREMENTS:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in finance, economics, computer science, business, or related field (with a strong academic record).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;4+ years of experience in market data management within a financial services or trading environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of exchange data licensing, entitlements, and governance policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to negotiate contracts and manage vendor relationships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with market data platforms, feed technologies, and integration processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of global trading markets and regulatory requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent relationship management and communication skills for both external partners and internal stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem-solving skills with the ability to anticipate issues and propose solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detail-oriented with the ability to track policy changes and ensure operational compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Project management skills, including leading cross-functional initiatives and meeting deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical proficiency to work with technology teams on feed configuration, data integration, and system optimization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Self-starter with a proactive approach to identifying trends, risks, and opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work under pressure in a fast-paced, dynamic trading environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative mindset with the capability to bridge communication between technical and non-technical teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to the highest ethical standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

