&lt;p&gt;Product Designer, Knowledge Graph Intelligence&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Career with Point72’s Compliance Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Point72 Compliance department is an industry-leading team of compliance professionals who support global investment and trading activities by establishing and enforcing the firm’s compliance policies, providing real-time advice, and conducting pre- and post-trade surveillance. Our team is essential to Point72’s success and we provide mentorship, a growth path, and the opportunity for a long-term career with us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Product Designer, you will join our Knowledge Graph Intelligence team, which focuses on developing technical applications for investment operations. Specifically, you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute the design process for new features and improvements, from concept to delivery, for our suite of investment applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with product managers, engineers, and stakeholders to understand requirements and translate them into user-centered design solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct user research and usability testing to gather insights and validate design decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create wireframes, prototypes, and high-fidelity designs that adhere to and contribute to our design system.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advocate for UX best practices while fostering a culture of design thinking and customer-centricity across the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Measure and analyze user engagement to identify opportunities for product improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay abreast of UX trends, tools, and technologies, and share knowledge with the team to foster innovation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What’s required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5 years of experience in UX design, with a proven track record of delivering user-centric solutions in an agile development environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A degree in UX design, human-computer interaction, or a related field, or equivalent practical experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong portfolio showcasing expertise in UX design, particularly in the context of web applications for financial services or similar complex domains.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated proficiency in design and prototyping tools, such as Figma and/or Adobe XD, and a solid understanding of HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and collaboration skills, with the ability to articulate design decisions and incorporate feedback from multiple stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion for understanding the needs of users with experience conducting user research and usability testing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Commitment to the highest ethical standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We take care of our people&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We invest in our people, their careers, their health, and their well-being. When you work here, we provide:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fully-paid health care benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous parental and family leave policies&lt;/li&gt;
