&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL DO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build the core user interfaces and backend services that power the firm’s treasury workflows, delivering high-performance tools that expose large datasets to traders and operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the end-to-end delivery of new features: translate business problems into user-centric designs, implement front-end and back-end components, and ship to production&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Shape the vision and roadmap for treasury user interfaces, driving decisions about data presentation, interactivity, and user experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop single-page applications and reusable front-end components that make complex treasury data explorable and actionable in real time&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and implement backend REST services with efficient server-side pagination and filtering to support large-scale client-side controls&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize performance and scalability across the stack, including data serialization, API throughput, and client rendering for large tables and charts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate closely with treasury stakeholders, quantitative analysts, and product managers to refine requirements, validate designs, and prioritize impactful features&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive engineering quality through code reviews, automated testing, continuous integration, and deployment practices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Investigate and resolve production incidents, improve observability, and lead post-incident reviews to prevent recurrence&lt;/li&gt;
