&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Career with Point72’s Tax team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Point72’s Tax team sits at the center of a sophisticated global investment platform, overseeing tax compliance and planning across 30+ hedge funds, 75+ private equity and management companies, high-net-worth individuals, and tax-exempt organizations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team partners closely with Big Four accounting firms and leading external advisors to manage the preparation and review of partnership, corporate, individual, international, and state tax filings. Beyond compliance, the group leads tax research, planning initiatives, and firmwide projects, collaborating across the organization to address complex tax issues in a dynamic investment environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a member of the Private Equity and Venture Capital (PEVC) Tax team, you will focus on fund and investment-level tax matters and deepen your experience in private equity and venture capital taxation. Specifically, you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist the PEVC Tax team with all aspects of the tax compliance process including but not limited to operating companies, family partnerships, private equity, and venture capital funds&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review tax return extensions, federal and state income tax returns, and investor Schedule K‑1s for private equity venture capital funds and related entities, coordinating with external service providers as needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gain exposure to ad‑hoc consulting and analysis on matters such as fund and investment structuring, carried interest, waterfall allocations, partner economics, and transaction-related tax considerations, as required&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and/or review tax workpapers, with a focus on designing and implementing an automated process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collect, review, and draft materials in response to audits conducted by domestic (U.S.), federal and state, and international taxing authorities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the team with tax research and analysis on day‑to‑day issues impacting PE/VC funds and related entities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work in a collaborative, roll-up-your-sleeves environment, bringing a sense of urgency and attention to detail to requests and projects&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in automating and enhancing processes related to the preparation and review of tax workpapers, supporting schedules, and forms through the use of Point72’s internal proprietary tax technology and through the build-out and/or integration of new systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
