&lt;li&gt;7+ years of experience in U.S. taxation, with a focus on high-net-worth individuals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in accounting or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CPA licensure or roadmap to obtain the designation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience responding to tax notices and audit inquiries from federal and state taxing authorities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, including experience reviewing complex financial and tax documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced Excel skills and the ability to quickly learn new systems and proprietary software.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to interact effectively with internal teams and external advisors.&lt;/li&gt;
